ğŸ§  What Are Anagram Strings?

Two strings are called anagrams if:
They contain the same characters with the same frequency, but possibly in a different order.

âœ… Conditions for Anagram Strings:
    Same length
    Same characters
    Same frequency of each character
    Order does NOT matter

ğŸ” Example of Anagram Strings:
String 1	String 2	Are Anagrams?	Reason
"listen"	"silent"	âœ… Yes	        Same letters, rearranged
"evil"	    "vile"	    âœ… Yes	        All characters and counts match
"triangle"	"integral"	âœ… Yes	        Same set of characters
"rat"	    "car"	    âŒ No	        Different characters

âŒ Not Anagrams:

"aab" and "abb" â†’ Not anagrams because character counts differ (a appears twice in one, once in the other).
"hello" and "helo" â†’ Not anagrams because one letter is missing.

Brute Force Approach -

if both string length is diff then return false
else create 2 maps and iterate first string and keep its all chars and frequencey in map
and similarly do for another string in another map
and then check if both maps are equal or not
If equal then strings are anagram of each other
and if not equals then strings are not anagram of each other and return false


