Group Anagrams brute force approach -

âœ… Approach: Sorted string ko key bana ke group karna

end me map will look like below

{
  "aet": ["eat", "tea", "ate"],
  "ant": ["tan", "nat"],
  "abt": ["bat"]
}

ğŸ¥‡ Step 1:
    Ek Map<String, List<String>> banao.
    Key: Sorted string (jaise "eat" â†’ "aet")
    Value: List of original strings jo us key se match karte hain

ğŸ¥ˆ Step 2:

    Array ke har string pe loop chalao:

    Har word ko char array me convert karo
    âœ "eat" â†’ ['e', 'a', 't']

    Us array ko sort karo
    âœ ['a', 'e', 't']

    Fir use wapas string me convert karo
    âœ "aet" â† Ye ban gaya tumhara grouping key


ğŸ¥‰ Step 3:

    Check karo ki wo key map me already hai ya nahi:
    Agar hai, to us list me current string add karo
    Agar nahi, to nayi list banao aur string usme daalo

ğŸ Step 4:
    Map ke sabhi values (lists) uthao aur result me daal do.